==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wer-alt-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[werold]] (Dutch [[wereld]]), Old High German [[weralt]] (German [[Welt]]), Old Norse [[verǫld]] (Swedish [[värld]]).  The Germanic noun was a compound made up of ''*wera-'' (Old English [[wer]]) + ''*alt-'' (Old English [[eald]]), so literally ‘age of man’.

